                            <comment id="13180273" author="cmale" created="Thu, 5 Jan 2012 10:41:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing this out, I&apos;ll wrap it up shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13180275" author="thetaphi" created="Thu, 5 Jan 2012 10:44:54 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;It look like DEFAULT_RESPONSE_WRITERS never called init method in org.apache.solr.core.SolrCore&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is this a bug or not?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13180277" author="cmale" created="Thu, 5 Jan 2012 10:47:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think its definitely something we should correct as well.  The Writers in the DEFAULT_RESPONSE_WRITERS list should be being init&apos;d too (in case we ever add in further init logic to them).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13203213" author="cmale" created="Wed, 8 Feb 2012 03:03:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch based on Gasol&apos;s which addresses the Content-Type missing in JSONResponseWriter, and also init&apos;s the default QueryResponseWriters.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ready to go.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13207236" author="hossman" created="Mon, 13 Feb 2012 21:38:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Chris: +1, commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
